# DEV ONLY — never used in packaged builds (stripped at build time).
# Production desktop always uses authenticated /api/* with server-side OPENAI_API_KEY.
VITE_OPENAI_API_KEY=
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
VITE_LEGAL_BASE_URL=https://landed-ai.com
# Always the deployed billing API (desktop ignores localhost for checkout)
VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://landed-ai.com
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=821453006387-snrakrrq6n17m5pde2nfshmnf8nanmc6.apps.googleusercontent.com

# Billing uses the Next.js API on landed-ai.com — Stripe keys live in repo root .env / Vercel env
# Webhook: https://landed-ai.com/api/webhooks/stripe

# Run `supabase db push` from repo root after linking your Supabase project.
# Migrations live in supabase/migrations/.
#
# Google OAuth (required for "Continue with Google"):
# 1. Google Cloud → OAuth 2.0 Web client → Authorized redirect URIs (exact):
#    https://epeitwkgbfabevxyznrh.supabase.co/auth/v1/callback
#    (Do NOT put landed://auth/callback here — that goes in Supabase redirect URLs.)
# 2. From repo root: GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=GOCSPX-... ./scripts/setup-google-auth.sh
# 3. If you see redirect_uri_mismatch: ./scripts/fix-google-oauth-redirect.sh --open
# 4. Desktop Google OAuth uses http://127.0.0.1:42817/auth/callback (Electron loopback).
#    Add that URL in Supabase → Auth → URL Configuration → Redirect URLs if sign-in stalls.
#    Web bridge fallback: http://localhost:3000/auth/callback (run `npm run desktop:dev`).
